          <h2>Why Newmarket Chinese-Canadian Families Choose a Mandarin-Speaking Lawyer</h2>
          <p>Working with a family lawyer in a language you don't fully control creates real risks — details get lost, nuances are missed, and the emotional weight of what you're going through doesn't fully come across. Miao He communicates directly in Mandarin, ensuring that the full picture reaches the legal process.</p>

          <h3>No Interpreter: Lower Cost, Better Accuracy</h3>
          <p>Many Chinese-Canadian clients work with English-speaking lawyers and hire a separate interpreter for consultations and court appearances. This adds cost — interpreter fees can run $100–$200 per hour — and introduces the risk that critical details are imprecisely translated. Miao He speaks Mandarin directly. The savings are real, and so is the accuracy.</p>

          <h3>Courthouse Familiarity: Newmarket Superior Court</h3>
          <p>The Superior Court of Justice — Newmarket Courthouse (50 Eagle Street West) handles York Region family law matters. Miao He has extensive experience at this court — its scheduling practices, the conference process, how motions are handled, and what judges in this jurisdiction expect from counsel. This local knowledge translates into more efficient case management and better-prepared appearances.</p>

          <h3>Divorce: Contested and Uncontested</h3>
          <p>An uncontested divorce — where both spouses agree on all terms — can be completed in Ontario in as little as 4 to 6 months without a court appearance. A contested divorce, where spouses disagree on property, support, or custody, takes significantly longer and requires court appearances. Miao He advises clients honestly on which path makes sense for their situation and guides the full process in Mandarin.</p>

          <h3>Child Custody and Parenting Plans</h3>
          <p>Newmarket Chinese-Canadian families often face custody questions that involve cultural considerations: whether children can travel to China for extended visits, Chinese-language schooling, grandparent involvement in care. Miao He builds Parenting Plans that address these specifics in legally binding terms — reducing the likelihood of future disputes by being precise about what each party can and cannot do.</p>

          <h3>Property Division and York Region Real Estate</h3>
          <p>York Region properties — detached homes, investment properties, and properties with parental contributions — are subject to Ontario's Net Family Property Equalization rules. Miao He ensures accurate valuation at the correct separation date, proper exclusion of pre-marital and gifted assets, and full disclosure of all assets including those held in China.</p>

